    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-08-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-08-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="136" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 136.</note>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Davis</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Bancroft</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. <hi rend="smallcaps">219.]</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic"> Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-08-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 17, 1870.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Inclosed you will find a copy of Mr.
                            Washburne’s dispatch, No. 238, on the subject of the departure of North
                            Germans from French territory.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * * * *</p>
                <p>Mr. Washburne’s course in this correspondence has been approved. He
                            advises the Department, in a dispatch received to-day, that he has
                            received a reply to his note, which will be forwarded, he says, by the
                            next post. As soon as it is received here, a copy will be sent you.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. C. B. DAVIS.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>[For this inclosure see Mr. Washburne’s No. 238, dated July 29, under
                                the title “France,” <hi rend="italic">ante.</hi>]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
